Key Match Events: Saud Shakeel scored 68 runs off 52 balls, leading Pakistan's middle order recovery from 38 for 3.
Haris Rauf took 3 wickets for 43 runs in Pakistan's bowling effort.
Vikramjit Singh and Bas de Leede scored 52 and 67 runs respectively for Netherlands, setting a promising start but ultimately falling for 205.
Pre-Game Insights: Pakistan captain Babar Azam emphasized the importance of the bowling attack taking early wickets.
Scott Edwards, Netherlands captain, highlighted the importance of support from the lower order.
Post-Match Reflections: Pakistan captain Babar Azam expressed satisfaction with the team's performance and credited the bowlers for their early success.
Saud Shakeel, Player of the Match, thanked his coaching staff for boosting his confidence and highlighted his improvement in building innings.
Scott Edwards, Netherlands captain, acknowledged the strong bowling efforts of Pakistan but felt disappointed with the team's inability to capitalize on a promising start.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was played at the Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad.
Pakistan won by 81 runs, securing a convincing victory.
Haris Rauf's decisive wicket-taking performance contributed significantly to the win.
